 intervention"}, {"duration": 4.68, "start": 789.519, "text": "and clamp our output to positive 160 we"}, {"duration": 3.639, "start": 791.88, "text": "see our Trend reverse with low"}, {"duration": 3.88, "start": 794.199, "text": "questionable and poor moving"}, {"duration": 4.68, "start": 795.519, "text": "significantly up in the rankings so"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 798.079, "text": "increasing the output of neuron 1393 in"}, {"duration": 4.64, "start": 800.199, "text": "layer 21 increases Jemma's trust in"}, {"duration": 5.241, "start": 802.639, "text": "Wikipedia and reversing its outputs"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 804.839, "text": "increases its skepticism or doubt so"}, {"duration": 4.959, "start": 807.88, "text": "have we found a specific gem neuron that"}, {"duration": 5.84, "start": 809.88, "text": "controls trust or in Reverse doubting or"}, {"duration": 4.36, "start": 812.839, "text": "skeptical Behavior another way to test"}, {"duration": 3.76, "start": 815.72, "text": "this idea is to search for other"}, {"duration": 5.88, "start": 817.199, "text": "examples of text that caus neuron 1393"}, {"duration": 5.919, "start": 819.48, "text": "and layer 21 to Output large values if"}, {"duration": 3.88, "start": 823.079, "text": "we found a doubting or skeptical neuron"}, {"duration": 4.601, "start": 825.399, "text": "then the text that causes this neuron to"}, {"duration": 5.161, "start": 826.959, "text": "maximally activate should reflect this"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 830.0, "text": "searching through 100,000 examples from"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 832.12, "text": "the pile data set and collecting the"}, {"duration": 5.039, "start": 834.24, "text": "examples that maximally activate neuron"}, {"duration": 5.0, "start": 836.68, "text": "1393 these examples seem to have nothing"}, {"duration": 4.161, "start": 839.279, "text": "to do with doubt or skepticism and"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 841.68, "text": "instead seem to correspond to examples"}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 843.44, "text": "of capital letters in acronyms or proper"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 845.68, "text": "nouns in various"}, {"duration": 5.08, "start": 847.6, "text": "context we've reached our first big"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 849.92, "text": "hurdle in interpreting Gemma clearly"}, {"duration": 4.079, "start": 852.68, "text": "this neuron has some bearing on the"}, {"duration": 3.919, "start": 854.16, "text": "model's doubting or skeptical Behavior"}, {"duration": 3.44, "start": 856.759, "text": "but the examples that this neuron"}, {"duration": 4.161, "start": 858.079, "text": "responds most strongly to are related to"}, {"duration": 4.44, "start": 860.199, "text": "a seemingly unrelated"}, {"duration": 3.92, "start": 862.24, "text": "concept this phenomenon of single"}, {"duration": 3.2, "start": 864.639, "text": "neurons and large language models"}, {"duration": 3.919, "start": 866.16, "text": "corresponding to multiple seemingly"}, {"duration": 4.761, "start": 867.839, "text": "unrelated Concepts has been observed"}, {"duration": 4.2, "start": 870.079, "text": "across a broad range of models and is"}, {"duration": 3.56, "start": 872.6, "text": "known as polys"}, {"duration": 3.721, "start": 874.279, "text": "semanticity interestingly polys"}, {"duration": 4.039, "start": 876.16, "text": "semanticity occurs much more frequently"}, {"duration": 4.399, "start": 878.0, "text": "in language models than in Vision"}, {"duration": 3.481, "start": 880.199, "text": "models specific neurons and vision"}, {"duration": 3.36, "start": 882.399, "text": "models have been shown to respond"}, {"duration": 5.399, "start": 883.68, "text": "uniquely to things like faces cars and"}, {"duration": 5.921, "start": 885.759, "text": "many many more recognizable Concepts in"}, {"duration": 4.601, "start": 889.079, "text": "2022 Chris Ola and the team at anthropic"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 891.68, "text": "published an interesting hypothesis to"}, {"duration": 4.159, "start": 893.68, "text": "explain this observed polys semanticity"}, {"duration": 3.279, "start": 896.24, "text": "the idea is that language models are"}, {"duration": 3.8, "start": 897.839, "text": "able to learn more con Concepts than"}, {"duration": 3.921, "start": 899.519, "text": "they have neurons essentially by"}, {"duration": 4.32, "start": 901.639, "text": "representing Concepts using specific"}, {"duration": 5.319, "start": 903.44, "text": "combinations of neurons the team calls"}, {"duration": 4.601, "start": 905.959, "text": "this idea superposition so Concepts may"}, {"duration": 4.481, "start": 908.759, "text": "be spread across multiple neurons and"}, {"duration": 4.48, "start": 910.56, "text": "layers in Gemma if we can't isolate"}, {"duration": 4.039, "start": 913.24, "text": "Concepts and behaviors to certain layers"}, {"duration": 5.239, "start": 915.04, "text": "or neurons how can we hope to understand"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 917.279, "text": "or control language models one option is"}, {"duration": 3.841, "start": 920.279, "text": "to modify the model architecture to"}, {"duration": 4.841, "start": 922.399, "text": "encourage or Force the model to have"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 924.12, "text": "fewer neurons fire for any given input"}, {"duration": 3.399, "start": 927.24, "text": "ideally this would stop the model from"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 928.68, "text": "spreading Concepts across multiple"}, {"duration": 4.721, "start": 930.639, "text": "neurons the anthropic team tried this in"}, {"duration": 4.519, "start": 933.24, "text": "2023 and found that models still"}, {"duration": 4.76, "start": 935.36, "text": "exhibited polys semanticity even in"}, {"duration": 5.2, "start": 937.759, "text": "extreme cases where they forced only a"}, {"duration": 4.279, "start": 940.12, "text": "single neuron to fire at a time another"}, {"duration": 3.281, "start": 942.959, "text": "option is to try to figure out which"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 944.399, "text": "combinations of neurons respond to"}, {"duration": 5.44, "start": 946.24, "text": "certain Concepts perhaps neuron 1393 and"}, {"duration": 4.48, "start": 949.44, "text": "layer 21 combined with other neurons"}, {"duration": 5.0, "start": 951.68, "text": "will cleanly represent the concept of"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 953.92, "text": "Doubt but how can we possibly figure out"}, {"duration": 3.399, "start": 956.68, "text": "which combinations of neurons map"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 958.48, "text": "cleanly to which"}, {"duration": 4.2, "start": 960.079, "text": "Concepts remarkably there is a simple"}, {"duration": 4.2, "start": 962.48, "text": "model that we can train to learn these"}, {"duration": 4.281, "start": 964.279, "text": "mappings called a sparse"}, {"duration": 4.399, "start": 966.68, "text": "autoencoder if the superposition"}, {"duration": 4.48, "start": 968.56, "text": "hypothesis is true we should be able to"}, {"duration": 4.081, "start": 971.079, "text": "take some combination of the outputs of"}, {"duration": 3.76, "start": 973.04, "text": "the neurons in a given layer and this"}, {"duration": 3.44, "start": 975.16, "text": "combination of neurons should respond"}, {"duration": 4.12, "start": 976.8, "text": "very strongly to a single specific"}, {"duration": 3.52, "start": 978.6, "text": "concept and respond very minimally to"}, {"duration": 3.68, "start": 980.92, "text": "all other"}, {"duration": 4.159, "start": 982.12, "text": "Concepts most sparse auto encoders used"}, {"duration": 3.44, "start": 984.6, "text": "today in mechanistic interpretability"}, {"duration": 3.321, "start": 986.279, "text": "work by hooking them up to a specific"}, {"duration": 3.52, "start": 988.04, "text": "point in the model"}, {"duration": 3.719, "start": 989.6, "text": "such as the output of a certain layer or"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 991.56, "text": "the residual stream at a certain"}, {"duration": 4.721, "start": 993.319, "text": "location so if we take the output of the"}, {"duration": 4.759, "start": 995.56, "text": "21st layer of Gemma where Gemma started"}, {"duration": 4.279, "start": 998.04, "text": "exhibiting doubting Behavior the idea"}, {"duration": 4.721, "start": 1000.319, "text": "here is that we can take these 234"}, {"duration": 4.681, "start": 1002.319, "text": "neuron outputs and find some combination"}, {"duration": 4.2, "start": 1005.04, "text": "of these outputs that cleanly responds"}, {"duration": 4.279, "start": 1007.0, "text": "to examples of doubt we can take a"}, {"duration": 4.039, "start": 1009.24, "text": "single combination of our outputs by"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 1011.279, "text": "multiplying our neuron outputs by a new"}, {"duration": 4.761, "start": 1013.279, "text": "waiting Vector of length 2304 where each"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 1016.399, "text": "entry in the waiting tells us how much"}, {"duration": 4.08, "start": 1018.04, "text": "of each neuron output to take we can"}, {"duration": 3.841, "start": 1020.639, "text": "then add these results together to give"}, {"duration": 4.16, "start": 1022.12, "text": "us a final output value that should"}, {"duration": 4.559, "start": 1024.48, "text": "correspond to the overall strength of"}, {"duration": 5.039, "start": 1026.28, "text": "our concept now per the superposition"}, {"duration": 4.88, "start": 1029.039, "text": "hypothesis our model represents more"}, {"duration": 5.24, "start": 1031.319, "text": "Concepts than it has neurons so we need"}, {"duration": 5.481, "start": 1033.919, "text": "more than 2,34 of these waiting vectors"}, {"duration": 4.4, "start": 1036.559, "text": "to tease out all the different concepts"}, {"duration": 4.919, "start": 1039.4, "text": "let's try modeling"}, {"duration": 6.72, "start": 1040.959, "text": "16,384 different concepts so we need"}, {"duration": 5.041, "start": 1044.319, "text": "16,384 separate vectors we can stack all"}, {"duration": 5.88, "start": 1047.679, "text": "of these waiting vectors into a single"}, {"duration": 5.52, "start": 1049.36, "text": "new Matrix of Dimension 2304 by 16 384"}, {"duration": 4.521, "start": 1053.559, "text": "where each column represents the"}, {"duration": 5.76, "start": 1054.88, "text": "contributions of our 234 neurons to each"}, {"duration": 4.56, "start": 1058.08, "text": "concept multiplying our neuron output"}, {"duration": 4.32, "start": 1060.64, "text": "vector by our waiting Matrix yields a"}, {"duration": 4.159, "start": 1062.64, "text": "new Vector of length"}, {"duration": 4.28, "start": 1064.96, "text": "16,384 where each entry should"}, {"duration": 4.721, "start": 1066.799, "text": "correspond to the strength of a specific"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 1069.24, "text": "concept now how do we learn the weights"}, {"duration": 4.96, "start": 1071.52, "text": "for our new Matrix that will allow us to"}, {"duration": 5.079, "start": 1073.48, "text": "cleanly map neurons to concepts for any"}, {"duration": 4.4, "start": 1076.48, "text": "given input example we know that we only"}, {"duration": 5.841, "start": 1078.559, "text": "want a very small number of our"}, {"duration": 5.08, "start": 1080.88, "text": "16,384 Concepts to be active at once"}, {"duration": 4.32, "start": 1084.4, "text": "otherwise we' run into the same polys"}, {"duration": 5.12, "start": 1085.96, "text": "semanticity issue we saw with neurons"}, {"duration": 4.76, "start": 1088.72, "text": "this is where the sparsity comes in"}, {"duration": 4.24, "start": 1091.08, "text": "sparse autoencoders work by forcing most"}, {"duration": 4.439, "start": 1093.48, "text": "of the values in our concept Vector to"}, {"duration": 4.2, "start": 1095.32, "text": "be zero or near zero and then using the"}, {"duration": 4.0, "start": 1097.919, "text": "remaining values to reconstruct the"}, {"duration": 4.399, "start": 1099.52, "text": "original input reconstruction of the"}, 